nodes.task:
Fix issues #7 (soft 404 / unknown nested routes return 200), #8 (generic <title> on every route), and #11 (no OG/Twitter meta).

Current state of frontend/src/app/[...slug]/page.tsx: it just re-exports the home page (`export { default } from '../page'`), so every URL renders the terminal and returns 200. The root page.tsx is a 'use client' component. The actual command-allowlist logic lives in frontend/src/lib/websocket.ts (PROJECT_ALIASES, BLOCKED_HEADS, pathToCommand).

Approach:
1. Create frontend/src/lib/routes.ts (NEW). Single source of truth for valid top-level commands. Export:
   - `KNOWN_COMMANDS`: Set<string> of every accepted top-level command. Include: 'welcome','about','contact','blog','projects','resume','help','flt','agentelo','trade-up-bot','skyblock-qol','term-site','stm32-games','dotfiles','hone','harness'. Source: read container/scripts/*.sh filenames (each `<name>.sh` exposes a `<name>` command). Hardcode the list rather than reading the FS at request time.
   - `BLOG_SLUG_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/`
   - `isValidPath(pathname: string): boolean` — returns true if the path is a known route. Logic:
     • '/' or '' → true
     • Strip leading 't/' if present (treat /t/foo as /foo)
     • Strip leading 'projects/' if present (legacy alias path)
     • Split on '/'. The FIRST segment must be in KNOWN_COMMANDS. If there is a second segment, it's only allowed when the first segment is 'blog' (slug must match BLOG_SLUG_PATTERN) or 'projects' (alias must be in KNOWN_COMMANDS). Reject 3+ segments.
     • Returns false for `/about/anything`, `/t/notacommand`, `/blog/has spaces`, `/foo/bar/baz`.
   - `getPageMetadata(pathname: string): { title: string; description: string }` — returns per-route metadata. Examples:
     • '/' → { title: 'twaldin — interactive terminal portfolio', description: 'Timothy Waldin\'s portfolio: live terminal, blog, projects.' }
     • '/about' or '/t/about' → { title: 'about — twaldin', description: 'About Timothy Waldin.' }
     • '/blog' → { title: 'blog — twaldin', description: 'Posts from Timothy Waldin.' }
     • '/blog/<slug>' → { title: '<slug> — twaldin blog', description: 'Blog post: <slug>.' }
     • '/projects' → { title: 'projects — twaldin', description: 'Projects by Timothy Waldin.' }
     • '/projects/<alias>' or '/<alias>' (where alias is a project) → { title: '<alias> — twaldin', description: 'Project: <alias>.' }
     • Other valid commands → { title: '<cmd> — twaldin', description: 'twaldin terminal — <cmd>.' }
2. Convert frontend/src/app/[...slug]/page.tsx to a server component:
   ```
   import { notFound } from 'next/navigation';
   import type { Metadata } from 'next';
   import { isValidPath, getPageMetadata } from '@/lib/routes';
   import Home from '../page';

   type Params = { slug?: string[] };

   export async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: Promise<Params> }): Promise<Metadata> {
     const { slug } = await params;
     const pathname = '/' + (slug ?? []).join('/');
     const m = getPageMetadata(pathname);
     return {
       title: m.title,
       description: m.description,
       openGraph: { title: m.title, description: m.description, url: `https://tim.waldin.net${pathname}`, siteName: 'twaldin', type: 'website' },
       twitter: { card: 'summary', title: m.title, description: m.description },
     };
   }

   export default async function CatchAll({ params }: { params: Promise<Params> }) {
     const { slug } = await params;
     const pathname = '/' + (slug ?? []).join('/');
     if (!isValidPath(pathname)) notFound();
     return <Home />;
   }
   ```
   Note Next 15 params is a Promise — keep it that way.
3. Create frontend/src/app/not-found.tsx (NEW). A simple server component that returns a styled 404 message in the same terminal aesthetic. Set `export const metadata = { title: '404 — twaldin' }`. It should NOT mount the live terminal (that defeats the purpose). Static HTML only, link back to '/'.
4. Update frontend/src/app/page.tsx (the root home page). Add `export async function generateMetadata` is NOT possible because page.tsx is `'use client'`. Instead, ADD the metadata to frontend/src/app/layout.tsx by importing getPageMetadata and using it in a generateMetadata function on layout. BUT layout.tsx already exports a static `metadata` object — replace it with `export async function generateMetadata` that returns the homepage metadata + opengraph + twitter from getPageMetadata('/').
5. In frontend/src/app/layout.tsx, also add a default OG image link in the `<head>` (not strictly required but mentioned by issue #11). Skip the image for now and just add OG/Twitter text fields via the metadata object — image can come later.

Tests (TDD — write first, watch fail, then make pass):
- frontend/src/lib/__tests__/routes.test.ts — unit tests for isValidPath:
  • '/'  → true
  • '/about' → true
  • '/t/about' → true
  • '/blog' → true
  • '/blog/some-post' → true
  • '/projects' → true
  • '/projects/flt' → true
  • '/flt' → true (top-level project alias)
  • '/notacommand' → false
  • '/about/anything' → false
  • '/t/notacommand' → false
  • '/blog/has spaces' → false (or any other invalid slug)
  • '/foo/bar/baz' → false
- and unit tests for getPageMetadata returning the right title/description shape for each of the above valid paths.
- The frontend test runner is whatever is already wired up. Check frontend/package.json for the test script. If no test runner is configured, install vitest as a devDep (pnpm add -D vitest @vitest/ui or whichever package manager the lockfile uses) and add a `test` script. If you can't add a test runner without breaking the build, write the tests anyway and document in coder.md that they need a runner — the unit tests are simple enough to be smoke-validated by `node --experimental-vm-modules` if pressed.

Manual verification:
- `cd frontend && pnpm build` (or npm/yarn whichever lockfile shows). It must compile cleanly.
- `pnpm dev`, then `curl -I http://localhost:3000/notacommand` → expect HTTP/1.1 404.
- `curl -I http://localhost:3000/about` → expect HTTP/1.1 200.
- `curl -s http://localhost:3000/about | grep -o '<title>[^<]*</title>'` → expect `about — twaldin`, NOT the generic.
- `curl -s http://localhost:3000/about | grep -o 'og:title[^>]*'` → expect `og:title content="about — twaldin"`.

Commit messages: `refs #7`, `refs #8`, `refs #11` — can group into one or two commits.

flt workflow pass when tests are green, build passes, manual curl checks succeed, and your coder.md handoff is written.
